  "title": "Exam 3 - Math 122",
  "body": " Exam 3 - Math 122    You will solve each of the following problems, making sure to justify them with explanation and supporting computations. Keep the following in mind.   On all problems, you must show all work necessary to justify your solution.    On all problems, you must find a way to explain your reasoning. You must do this in complete sentences.         (25 pts.) Jojo has credit card debt of $1000. The card has an annual interest rate of 18% compounded every month, with a minimum monthly payment of $20. When a payment is made, the interest is computed before the payment is applied to the balance.   Determine Jojo's balance after 6 months if they pay $ per month. Show all work, and do not use any formulas that you cannot justify.    Use your answer to (a) to determine how much Jojo's monthly payment must be to pay off their debt in 6 months.         (35 pts.) A new car is purchased for $28000. Exactly year later, the value of the car is $23200.   Assume that the car's value in dollars, , years after purchase decays exponentially according to a model of form or (your choice). Determine the exact values of and either or in the model.    Using your model from (a), how many years will it take until the car's value is $10000?    Suppose that rather than having the car's value decay all the way to $0, the lowest dollar amount its value ever approaches is $500. What is your function if the model we use is either or (your choice)?         (15 pts.) A popular cruise ship sets sail in the Gulf of Mexico with 5000 passengers and crew on board. Unfortunately, five family members who board the ship are carrying a highly contagious virus. After interacting with many other passengers in the first few hours of the cruise, all five of them get very sick.  Let be the number of people who have acquired the virus days after the ship has left port. It turns out that a logistic function is a good model for , and thus we assume that for some positive constants , , and either or (your choice). Suppose that after 1 day, 20 people have gotten the virus.  Recall that we know and . In addition, assume that 5000 is the number of people who will eventually get sick. Use this information determine the exact values of , , and either or in the logistic model.      (25 pts.) The next problem is based on data given on the Google sheets file from Homework #9. You can find the link to the data on Blackboard on the document for Exam 3 in Exam Information & Resources or on the file for Homework #9. It is also right here: Advertising Data    Use Desmos to plot the data for TV advertising versus sales of the product.    Do regressions of your data with all six of the models we have studied in this course (i.e. linear, quadratic, exponential, logarithmic, vertically translated exponential [i.e. our temperature model], and logistic).    Which model fits the data best? Include any information from Desmos that supports your choice of model over the other models, and include the formula for the model that fits your data best. Explain why this model appears to be consistent with your plot on Desmos.    Use your model to predict how much of your TV advertising would be necessary to achieve 30,000 units in sales.       "
