  "body": " Final Exam - Math 122    You will solve each of the following problems, making sure to justify them with explanation and supporting computations. Keep the following in mind.   On all problems, you must show all work necessary to justify your solution.    On all problems, you must find a way to explain your reasoning. You must do this in complete sentences.         (34 pts.) For the following problem, note that for a polynomial , if is a root of (i.e. ), we say that has multiplicity if we can factor out from . So for the polynomial , the root 4 has multiplicity 5 and the root has multiplicity 3.   Find a formula for a polynomial that has roots at and , where both roots have multiplicity 2, and where the -intercept is at .    Find the formula for a polynomial that has degree 9, has roots of multiplicity 1 at and , has roots of multiplicity 2 at and , and has a root of multiplicity 3 at . Also, as , we have .    A polynomial has its graph given below. Determine a possible formula for . Explain why your formula is consistent with the graph below. In your explanation, explain why your function has the correct end behavior (i.e. what happens when and when ); explain why your formula has the correct -intercepts; and explain why the behavior of the graph at the -intercepts is consistent between your formula and the graph.     g(x)=-0.005*(x+3)^3*(x-1)^2*(x-4)      (2,1.25)              (27 pts.) A rectangular box is being constructed so that its base is twice as long as it is wide. In addition, the base and top of the box cost $2 per square foot while the sides cost $1.50 per square foot. We only want to spend $10 on materials for the box. Let be the width of the base, be the length of the base, and be the height of the box.   (3 pts.) What is the volume of the box?    (11 pts.) We know the total cost of the box is $10, but what is the total cost of the box in terms of , , and ?    (13 pts.) Write the volume of the box in terms of one variable.       "
