  "number": "",
  "title": "Homework Assignment #7 - Math 122",
  "body": " Homework Assignment #7 - Math 122    Due Sunday, 11\/8   These are the requirements for all homework assignments.   On all problems, you must show all work necessary to justify your solution.    On all problems, you must find a way to explain your reasoning. You must do this in complete sentences.    In your explanations and supporting work, do your best to demonstrate your understanding of the problem and the concepts used to solve them.    Make sure you carefully check the accuracy of your computations.   You may turn in your assignment as a hard copy in class, or you may submit your assignment electronically on Blackboard. If you turn in your assignment electronically, you must convert it to a PDF file .   Here are the problems for this assignment. Do not use any formulas that you cannot justify.    (70 pts.) Jojo has credit card debt of $1000. The card has an annual interest rate of 18% compounded every month, with a minimum monthly payment of $20. When a payment is made, the interest is computed before the payment is applied to the balance.   Determine Jojo's balance after 6 months if they always make the minimum monthly payment.    Determine Jojo's balance after 6 months if they pay $40 per month.    Compare the amount of money that Jojo paid in part (a) and part (b), and compare that to the difference in the amount of Jojo's debt that was paid off in part (a) and part (b). Briefly discuss anything that seemed disproportionate between the difference in payment versus the difference in debt paid off (i.e. did one of those differences seem proportionately smaller than the other?).    Determine Jojo's balance after 6 months if they pay $ per month.    Use your answer to part (d) to determine how much Jojo's monthly payment must be to pay off their debt in 6 months. Hint: What should your answer to part (d) be equal to?    Now suppose Jojo has credit card debt of $ with an annual interest rate of , compounded every month. Find a formula for how much Jojo's monthly payment needs to be in order to pay their debt off in 6 months. Show all work. I suggest using the same reasoning as you did in part (e).         Collaboration Reflection (5 pts.): For each of the following, write a 2-4 sentence reflection related to your collaboration with your group. You may write about positive contributions made and\/or ways that contributions could be improved.   Write a reflection on your contributions to the collaboration.    Write a reflection about your fellow collaborators' contributions.   You will not be penalized for any shortcomings you or your fellow group members had in your collaboration. Any good-faith effort you make to think about and explain your collaboration experience will be rewarded. I also will not share your reflections with anyone else in your group or the rest of the class without your permission.    If you want to read about some different ways of being a good collaborator, click on this rubric for some ideas. I will not be grading you according to how well you do on this rubric, only on how you reflect about your collaboration.  "
