  "body": " Resources for 10\/28    For the content of this class, you will be expected to be able to do the following:     Explain the properties , , and .    Use the above properties to solve equations involving variables in exponents.    Use the above properties to solve applied problems involving exponential functions.      Video & Activities for Logarithm Properties and Natural Logarithm  Below is a YouTube video on using the natural logarithm to solve equations. It is followed by a link to a set of activities that we will be working on in class. Please watch the video and do as many of the activities as you can before class.    Logarithm Properties and Natural Logarithm (Not on Quiz)  Solve the following equations using either or . Use it to give a decimal approximation for your answer.                      Feel free to post any questions you have on the FigJam board for the next class.    Video & Activities for Applications of Logarithms  Below is a YouTube video on applications of logarithms . It is followed by a link to a set of activities that we will be working on in class. Please watch the video and do as many of the activities as you can before class.    Logarithm Applications  For the following, justify any formulas you use that are not covered in class.     You invest $400 in an account that earns 4% interest annually. How long does it take for your account to be $1000?    When you inject a certain drug, it takes 25 hours for the concentration of the drug in the bloodstream to decrease by half. How long does it take for the concentration to decrease to 10% of its initial concentration?      Feel free to post any questions you have on the FigJam board for the next class.    Optional Reading  Section 3.5: pp. 192-198  Here is a link for the HTML version of Section 3.5 .   "
