  "body": " Exponential Applications    Solve the following application problems.     Suppose we invest money in an account with a fixed annual interest rate. After two years, we have $250 and after five years we have $400.   Find a formula for the amount that is in the account after years.    What is the interest rate on the account?    How much money did we start out with?         Suppose we own something that loses a fixed percentage of its value each year. After 3 years, it is worth $300, and after 7 years, it is worth $200.   Find a formula for the value that the item is worth after years.    What is the annual percentage that the value drops?    What was it worth at the beginning?       "
