  "body": " Polynomial Models    Find formulas for the following functions.     Suppose we have a box with length , width , and height .   Find a formula for the volume of the box.    Find a formula for the surface area of the box. Hint: Find the area of each side.    Suppose the box has a square bottom and a surface area of 36 ft . Find a formula for the volume in terms of one variable.    Suppose the box has a square bottom and has a volume of 20 ft . Find a formula for the surface area.         Suppose we have a cylindrical can of radius and height . Note that the area of a circle is given by and the circumference of a circle is given by .   Find a formula for the volume of the can. Hint: Find the area of the base first.    Find a formula for the surface area of the can: Hint: Find the area of the top, bottom, and side of the can. For the side, imagine what it looks like if you make a vertical cut and unroll it.    Suppose the can has a surface area of 16 in . Find a formula for the volume.    Suppose the can has volume 20 in . Find a formula for the surface area.         Do #1 when the box has an open top.    "
